          "Khaldoun Khelil"
        ],
        [],
        [
          "You had no formal magical education. As a mortal you served the secretive brotherhood known as House Tremere and you were happy the kind lords took you in off the streets of Vienna. It was only after you had tasted the blood of your master that you knew magic.  Unlike the other ghouls, the blood awakened somethign inside you.  You could conjure magical flame with ease and your master took great pride in shwoing you off to Lords and Pontifex.  You remained in Vienna for some years as the elders debated the source of your inner fire, but the Anarch Revolt brought the Assamites to the streets of Vienna.  It was in these brutal battles with the Assamite warriors that you truly proved yourself to the Tremere.  It was decided that you woudl be embraced by a promising Young Tremere adept in the Lure of the Flames once she had attained an appropiate rank.  You waited patiently for decades and were eventually embraced in the early 1800s. The embrace almost killed you as magical fire consumed your flesh and left you disfigured and in torpor. In fact, only the intervention of the Justicar Karl Schrekt was able to break your magical torpor and for that you still owe him a Major Boon. You rose through the ranks quickly and you've been trusted by the elders and leaders of the Clan with dangerous missions as a secret Astor. You've personally served multiple members of the Council of 7 who are aware that you are Unbondable and secretly praise your non-coerced devotion and loyalty. In LA you are here to continue 'feeding' your internal fire and to spy on the Chantry for Vienna if need be. The concentration of demonic energy in LA interests you as a source of power for the fire within, but you do not wish to be corrupted as you believe that Tremere himself has a grand design for the fire you wield."
        ],
        [
